text: Konstantinogradovka () is a rural locality (a village) and the administrative center of Konstantinogradovsky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 515 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 60 km from Sterlitamak. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlitamaksky District
title: Konstantinogradovka, Republic of Bashkortostan
